296.8	Cross-site_request_forgery	Cross-site request forgery	The attack works by including a link or script in a page that accesses a site to which the user is known (or is supposed) to have been authenticated. For example, one user, Bob, might be browsing a chat forum where another user, Fred, has posted a message. Suppose that Fred has crafted an HTML image element that references an action on Bob's bank's website (rather than an image file), e.g.,	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/eb/NVD-CVE-2007-1332.png/220px-NVD-CVE-2007-1332.png
